orientation','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Orientation',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(39,0,'orientation_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/orientation','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h3>This is a complicated process. You will go through three sections.</h3>\r\n          <p><span class=\"label\">First</span> Youâ€™ll interact with the core ideas of informed consent for the Sage Commons.</p>\r\n          <p><span class=\"label\">Second</span> Youâ€™ll read the informed consent agreement, and digitally sign it.</p>\r\n          <p><span class=\"label\">Third</span> Youâ€™ll be able to start participating in public genomics research by uploading data.</h3>\r\n          \r\n            <form name=\"orientation\" action=\"participation\" method=\"post\">\r\n            <fieldset>\r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"I understand, and want to proceed\">\r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(40,0,'rights','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'consent/rights','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Rights',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(41,0,'rights_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/rights','','\r\n','\r\n','','<form class=\"form-stacked\" id=\"consentForm\" name=\"rights\" action=\"video\" method=\"post\">\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n           <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label id=\"rightsCheckboxes\">These are the rights you are granting to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"qualified-researchers-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">qualified researchers</a></label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <ul class=\"inputs-list\">\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"researchCheckbox\" value=\"right_to_research\" />\r\n                    <span>Right to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"right-to-research-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">do research</a> with my data</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"redistributeCheckbox\" value=\"right_to_redistribute\" />\r\n                    <span>Right to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"right-to-redistribute-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">redistribute</a> my data</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"publishCheckbox\" value=\"right_to_publish\" />\r\n                    <span>Right to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"right-to-publish-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">publish the results of research</a> from my data</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"commercializeCheckbox\" value=\"commercialize\" />\r\n                    <span>Right to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"right-to-commercialize-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">commercialize products derived from research</a> on my data</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n              </ul>\r\n              <span class=\"help-block\">\r\n                All boxes must be checked to move forward in the consent process\r\n              </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"Next\">\r\n            </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"qualified-researchers-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Qualified Researchers</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Researchers who qualify to access the data you share will have gone through a process to make sure they\'re real people - not the kind of software robots that create spam in your mailbox - and will have signed a contract in which they commit not to identify you, not to harm you, and not to give your data to anyone else who hasn\'t signed the same terms. This is a low barrier of qualification, because we want a wide variety of researchers using Common Genomic Research data. We\'ll explain the risks later in this process, because it\'s important you understand them. By setting this barrier low, we increase the number of researchers, but we can always raise it if we - and you - decide it\'s necessary.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"right-to-research-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Right to Research</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Research is a broad term. It can mean anything from poking around inside data sets to see what clicks to using data in a large-scale, corporate clinical trial. Basically we are defining research as the use of your data to figure things out about biology, health, and more. It\'s about asking questions that are driven by data, or using data to formulate new questions. It\'s also about adding new data - new bits of information, what are often called annotations - that adds context to your data and makes it more useful in the assembly of data into knowledge. Research does not include the sale of your data as a product itself - your data will be free of charge in the CGR system, always, including to you.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"right-to-redistribute-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Right to Redistribute</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Data is easy to redistribute once it\'s in an online database, just like other forms of digital content such as music or ebooks. Controls on redistribution are complex, difficult to implement, expensive, and often fail to work (or at best, only work on nice people, not those who actively mean to get copies no matter what). Thus we are not implementing complex controls on redistribution, and indeed we are going to allow redistribution under a certain set of circumstances. A qualified researcher who accesses your data will have the right to redistribute it, but only to someone who has signed up to the terms of the system: don\'t re-identify people, don\'t do harm to people, publish results openly, and in turn, don\'t redistribute to someone who hasn\'t signed up for the same deal. We won\'t have the power to actively punish those who violate, but we will kick them out of the entire system and name them publicly. Violation of the terms will be a professional sin akin to plagiarism, which although not a legal crime, is an incredibly powerful control in its own right.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"right-to-publish-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Right to Publish</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Most traditional researchers are looking to make discoveries that they can publish in scholarly journals. This is a method of knowledge dissemination that is hundreds of years old, and one that is deeply enabled by the internet. We\'re simply making sure that this right to publish is explicit - that you know about it, and that researchers know about it. However, there is a twist - all those publications have to be made available for you, and the world, to read under \'Open Access\' terms. You\'ll learn more about that in the next part of the process.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"right-to-commercialize-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Right to Commercialize</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>One of the main reasons we\'re doing this is that we don\'t have enough products in health care - new therapies and medicines, new diagnostics, software tools that help us stay healthy, and more. Our explicit goal is to turn Common Genomic Research into the basis for new product discovery. This means that you are granting the right to researchers who make discoveries to turn them into products, without an expectation that you\'ll personally profit back from those products. Products are anything that can come out of your data: drugs, diagnostics, software apps, hardware, and more. Products are not your data itself. Your data is free, and always will be.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(42,0,'requests','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'consent/requests','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Requests',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(43,0,'requests_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/requests','','\r\n','\r\n','','<form class=\"form-stacked\" name=\"requests\" action=\"rights\" method=\"post\">\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n           <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n               <label id=\"conditions\">We will impose the following conditions on researchers through <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"terms-of-use-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">Terms of Use</a>, which either must be visible on the website that hosts your data or must be digitally signed by those who access your data.</label>\r\n                </div>\r\n                 <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <ul>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  Do not attempt to <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"re-identification-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">re-identify me</a>.\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"harm-prevention-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">Don\'t harm me</a>.\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"sharing-research-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">Share your research</a> from my data with the public under open access terms.\r\n                </li>\r\n              </ul>\r\n              <p>\r\n                However, there are limits to the power of Terms of Use, and there are no guarantees that users will respect all of these conditions. Please make sure to watch the entire video in the following stage of the consent process - it is vital that you understand these considerations if you are going to provide informed consent and participate in public genomics research.\r\n              </p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"I understand\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            \r\n            </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"your-requests-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Your Requests</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>By signing up for the Portable Consent process, you\'re signing up for a system that is a \'commons\' - meaning that while you\'ve granted some rights in the previous phase of the consent process, you\'re going to reserve some rights as well. These are behaviors you can request, and they\'ll be implemented via \'terms of use\' - a contract that researchers will have to sign to gain access to the system. You can read more about the terms of use below.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"re-identification-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Re-identification</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>We are quickly learning that with powerful computers and good mathematicians, it is increasingly possible to uniquely identify people inside large data sets. This is done every day with social media and in the \'app\' universe of phones, indeed, your personal data is the engine that powers the finances of the modern Web in many cases. Preventing re-identification is often one of the major goals of informed consent in its traditional context. Re-identification means that someone figures out that a given genotype or\' health record in the CGR system is actually yours, and connects it to your name, your email, or another piece of data that directly identifies you. Researchers will sign a contract in which they agree that, even if they were able to identify you, they won\'t do it.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"harm-prevention-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Harm Prevention</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Harm prevention is another major goal of informed consent systems. It\'s one of the primary reasons we have so much fragmented data. There are a lot of imagined - and real - harms for public or commonly available genomic data. Someone could use information from your health and genomic backgrounds to infer paternity or other features of your family history, make claims that could affect your employment, insurance, or other financial services, incriminate relatives, make and place synthetic DNA as evidence, or reveal propensity for a disease that has no treatment. Researchers will sign a contract in which they agree that, even if they were in position to harm you, such as working at an insurance company, they won\'t do it.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"sharing-research-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Sharing Research</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Since most research is published in scholarly journals, and most journals aren\'t available to the broader public due to cost and copyright concerns, researchers will have to commit to making their published research available under the Reproducible Research Standard. This means that the article itself must be \'Open Access\' - online, free of charge, and free of most copyright restrictions. It also means that any software and data that is needed to replicate or build on the research described in the article is also online, free of charge, and free of most copyright restrictions. This means you\'ll be able to read the article, and that others who might want to build on the research will be able to do so as well.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"terms-of-use-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Terms of Use</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Terms of use are the rules of the CGR system. They are embedded into a contract that researchers have to sign to access your data. These rules are legally binding on the researcher who signs them. If you\'ve used sites like eBay or PayPal, you\'ve used a website that uses terms of use to create community trust. If a researcher violates the terms of use, we will not only terminate their account, we\'ll name them publicly and make sure they don\'t come back.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(44,0,'video','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'consent/video','','\r\n','\r\n','','','\r\n','',0,0,'','Video',0,'','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(45,0,'video_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/video','','\r\n','\r\n','','<div class=\"well\">\r\n    \r\n<iframe id=\"ctrvideo\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/31686284?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;api=1&amp;player_id=ctrvideo\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen allowFullScreen></iframe>\r\n    \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"alert-message\" id=\"video_instructions\">You must finish watching the video to advance in the consent process.</div>\r\n\r\n<form class=\"form-stacked\" name=\"video\" action=\"understand\" method=\"post\">\r\n    \r\n    <fieldset>\r\n        \r\n         <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary disabled\" disabled=\'disabled\' value=\"Next\">\r\n         </div>\r\n    </fieldset>\r\n    \r\n</form>\r\n\r\n    <script src=\"http://a.vimeocdn.com/js/froogaloop2.min.js\"></script>\r\n\r\n<script>\r\n    \r\n(function(){\r\n \r\n    // Listen for the ready event for any vimeo video players on the page\r\n    var vimeoPlayers = document.querySelectorAll(\'iframe\'),\r\n        player;\r\n\r\n    for (var i = 0, length = vimeoPlayers.length; i < length; i++) {\r\n        player = vimeoPlayers[i];\r\n        $f(player).addEvent(\'ready\', ready);\r\n\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Utility function for adding an event. Handles the inconsistencies\r\n     * between the W3C method for adding events (addEventListener) and\r\n     * IE\'s (attachEvent).\r\n     */\r\n    function addEvent(element, eventName, callback) {\r\n        if (element.addEventListener) {\r\n            element.addEventListener(eventName, callback, false);\r\n        }\r\n        else {\r\n            element.attachEvent(eventName, callback, false);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * Called once a vimeo player is loaded and ready to receive\r\n     * commands. You can add events and make api calls only after this\r\n     * function has been called.\r\n     */\r\n    function ready(player_id) {\r\n        // Keep a reference to Froogaloop for this player\r\n        var froogaloop = $f(player_id);\r\n\r\n        /**\r\n         * Adds listeners for the events that are checked. Adding an event\r\n         * through Froogaloop requires the event name and the callback method\r\n         * that is called once the event fires.\r\n         */\r\n        function setupEventListeners() {\r\n            var finishChk = true;\r\n\r\n            function onFinish() {\r\n                if (finishChk) {\r\n                    froogaloop.addEvent(\'finish\', function(data) {\r\n                        $(\":submit\").removeClass(\'disabled\');\r\n                        $(\":submit\").removeAttr(\'disabled\');\r\n                        $(\"#video_instructions\").text(\"Click Next to continue the consent process.\");                                      $(\"#video_instructions\").addClass(\"success\");\r\n                    });\r\n                }\r\n                else {\r\n                    froogaloop.removeEvent(\'finish\');\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            // Calls the change event if the option is checked\r\n            // (this makes sure the checked events get attached on page load as well as on changed)\r\n            onFinish();\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        setupEventListeners();\r\n\r\n    }\r\n})();\r\n    \r\n</script>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(46,0,'understand','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'consent/understand','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Understand',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(47,0,'understand_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/understand','','\r\n','\r\n','','<div class=\"alert-message warning\">\r\n          If you don\'t feel like you know enough about public genetic research to move forward, or are uncomfortable now that you know, this is a good time to stop.\r\n          </div>\r\n          \r\n          <ul>\r\n              <li><a href=\"http://sagebase.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Please take me back to the Sage Bionetworks home page</a>.</li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://www.pgpstudy.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Please take me to resources on public genetics</a>.</li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://trentcenter.duke.edu/research/bioethics\" target=\"_blank\">Please take me to resources on bioethics and informed consent</a>.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n\r\n  \r\n     <!--           <div class=\"well\">\r\n                If you feel you are informed about public genetic research, please click the button <span class=\"label notice\">I understand</span> in order to proceed. You can return any time by keeping this window open or using this link: <a href=\"#\">TK</a>\r\n                </div>-->\r\n          \r\n            <form class=\"form-stacked\" name=\"understand\" action=\"affirm\" method=\"post\">\r\n              \r\n                <fieldset>\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"I understand, and want to proceed\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(48,0,'affirm','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'consent/affirm','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Affirm',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(49,0,'affirm_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/affirm','','\r\n','\r\n','','  <form class=\"form-stacked\" id=\"consentForm\" name=\"affirm\" action=\"agreement\" method=\"post\">\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n           <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n           <label id=\"affirmCheckboxes\">Tell us that you understand this informed consent process.</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <ul class=\"inputs-list\">\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"uncertaintyCheckbox\" value=\"understand_uncertainty_and_risk\" />\r\n                      <span>I understand <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"uncertainty-and-risk-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">the uncertainty and risk of public genetic research</a>.</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"publicCheckbox\" value=\"provide_data_for_public_research\" />\r\n                    <span>I provide <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"providing-consent-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">consent</a> for my data to be used in public genetic research</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"withdrawCheckboxes\" value=\"cannot_withdraw_data\" />\r\n                    <span>I understand that although I can <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"withdrawing-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">withdraw</a> at any time, I cannot withdraw data that has <a title=\"Click for more info\" data-controls-modal=\"withdrawing-data-modal\" data-backdrop=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\">already been distributed</a>.</span>\r\n                  </label>\r\n                </li>\r\n              </ul>\r\n              <span class=\"help-block\">\r\n                All boxes must be checked to create informed consent.\r\n              </span>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n                <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"I want to give consent\">&nbsp;<a href=\"[root]/consent/unsure\" class=\"btn\">I\'m not sure</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n               \r\n                </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"uncertainty-and-risk-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Uncertainty and Risk</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>The risks of public disclosure of your genetic and trait data, including your DNA sequence data, or other information you provide, could affect the employment, insurance and financial well-being or social interactions of you and your immediate family. The video you just watched, and the consent form, go through a long, but by necessity non-comprehensive, list of those risks. It\'s not comprehensive because we simply cannot imagine all the possible risks - they will change over time, and we do not have an infinite imagination. You should be prepared for these risks, and be willing to balance them against the benefit to scientific research of sharing. If you\'re not, please do not move forward to the next phase of the process.The Personal Genome Project perhaps summarizes the risks most succintly: in principle, someone could use information from your health and genomic backgrounds to infer paternity or other features of your family history, make claims that could affect your employment, insurance, or other financial services, incriminate relatives, make and place synthetic DNA as evidence, or reveal propensity for a disease that has no treatment. Please read carefully into Article VI of the consent form to see the detailed list provided there.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"providing-consent-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Providing Consent</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Consent means that you are providing a legally binding agreement that data you choose to upload will be available under Portable Legal Consent for distribution under the Common Genomics Research framework. Please do not digitally sign the consent form in the next phase if you do not wish to provide consent, or if you do not understand the ideas you have encountered in the process so far.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"withdrawing-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Withdrawing</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>It is possible to withdraw once you have provided consent. You would need to either contact the Common Genomics Research entity to which you uploaded your data and ask them to delete your data and notify those who have harvested it to delete your data, or to contact the harvesters of the data directly and ask them to delete your data. If you are contacting the harvesters, remember that they do not have your email or name, so you\'ll need to provide your Sage Bionetworks Common Identifier for them to know which record is yours and delete it. However, withdrawal and deletion of data may be of limited impact if that data has already been distributed to other parties under the Common Genomics Research framework.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"withdrawing-data-modal\" class=\"modal hide fade\">\r\n            <div class=\"modal-header\">\r\n              <a href=\"#\" class=\"close\">&times;</a>\r\n              <h3>Withdrawing Data</h3>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"modal-body\">\r\n              <p>Once any data or information about you is posted to the CGR public database, other organizations and individuals may acquire copies of it.  There will be no way to ensure that they will delete their copies of your data or information, or for Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project or  the CGR entity who runs an instance of the Consent framework to even know what copies of your data or information may exist.  Both Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project and  the CGR entity who runs an instance of the Consent framework will encourage researchers and other users to use the most current version of the CGR public database, but your data may be combined by Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project and/or its collaborators or other third parties in ways that will make it impossible to delete them from such datasets.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n              <div class=\"modal-footer\">\r\n            </div>\r\n</div>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(50,0,'agreement','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'consent/agreement','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Consent Agreement',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(51,0,'agreement_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/agreement','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h2>Consent Form</h2>\r\n\r\n(#(inherit:60)#)\r\n\r\n<div class=\"well\">\r\n(#(inherit:64)#)\r\n</div>\r\n    \r\n(#(inherit:61)#)\r\n\r\n(#(inherit:62)#)\r\n\r\n <form class=\"form-stacked\" id=\"consentForm\" name=\"agreement\" action=\"agreement_answers\" method=\"post\">\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n                <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <ul class=\"inputs-list\">\r\n                <li>\r\n                  <label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"understoodCheckbox\" value=\"have_read_and_understood_form\" />\r\n                      <span>I have read this entire informed consent form and I understand it completely. I confirm that I understand the purpose of this study, the study procedures, the possible risks and discomforts of participating in this study, the potential benefits that I may experience, and the alternatives to my participation in this study. All of my questions have been answered to my complete satisfaction.</span>\r\n                    </label>\r\n                  </li>\r\n                  <li><label>\r\n                    <input type=\"checkbox\" class=\"required\" name=\"termsCheckbox\" value=\"agree_to_terms_and_conditions\" />\r\n                      <span>I understand that by signing this informed consent form, I am acknowledging and agreeing to all of the terms and conditions of my participation set forth above, and I am providing my informed consent to participate in Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project.</span>\r\n                      </label>\r\n                  </li>\r\n                  </ul>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                \r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"full_name\">Name</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"full_name\" name=\"full_name\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" />\r\n                <span>Please enter your full name.</span>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          \r\n          <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"date\">Date</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge disabled\" id=\"date\" name=\"date\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" disabled />\r\n            </div>\r\n              \r\n              <script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n\r\nvar currentTime = new Date()\r\nvar month = currentTime.getMonth() + 1\r\nvar day = currentTime.getDate()\r\nvar year = currentTime.getFullYear()\r\n\r\n    $(\'#date\').val(year + \"/\" + month + \"/\" + day)\r\n</script>\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"actions\">\r\n                <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"I want to give consent\">&nbsp;<a href=\"[root]/consent/unsure\" class=\"btn\">I\'m not sure</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n              \r\n                </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(52,0,'register','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'consent/register','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Register',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(53,0,'register_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'consent/register','','SELECT ctr_agreements.full_name, email FROM ctr_agreements LEFT JOIN aiki_users on ctr_agreements.userid = aiki_users.userid WHERE aiki_users.userid = \'[userid]\' LIMIT 1\r\n','\r\n','',' <h3>Sage Commons User ID</h3>\r\n         \r\n         <h6>Your Consent Profile is 0% complete.</h6>\r\n          \r\n            <form class=\"form-stacked\" id=\"registerForm\" name=\"register\" action=\"register_answers\" method=\"Post\" autocomplete=\"off\">\r\n\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"full_name\">Name</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"full_name\" name=\"full_name\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" value=\"((full_name))\"/>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"email\">Email Address</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required email\" id=\"email\" name=\"email\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" value=\"((email))\"/>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"dob\">Date of Birth</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required date\" id=\"dob\" name=\"dob\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"mother\">Mother\'s Maiden Name</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"mother\" name=\"mother\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"movie\">Favorite Movie</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"movie\" name=\"movie\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n                 <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"username\">User ID</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge disabled\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" disabled=\"disabled\" value=\"[username]\"/>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"choose_password\">Password</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"choose_password\" name=\"choose_password\" size=\"30\" type=\"password\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"repeat_password\">Repeat Password</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"repeat_password\" name=\"repeat_password\" size=\"30\" type=\"password\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"Submit\">&nbsp;<button type=\"reset\" class=\"btn\">Reset</button>\r\n            </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(54,0,'home_header','default','body','div',1,'page-header',0,31,'homepage','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h1><a href=\"[root]\">Consent to Research</a> <small>Welcome</small></h1>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(55,0,'home_form','default','body','div',0,'',0,34,'homepage','','\r\n','\r\n','','<p><a href=\"alpha\" class=\"btn primary large\">Sign in using your Alpha Invitation Code &raquo;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"sage\" class=\"btn success large\">Sign in using your Sage Commons User ID&raquo;</a></p>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',1,'\r\n','alpha',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(77,0,'sage','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'sage','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Sign In',1,'(#(header:Location: [root]|false|301)#)\r\n','sage',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(56,0,'alpha','default','body','div',10,'',0,0,'alpha','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','Alpha Sign-in',1,'(#(header:Location: [root]/consent/orientation|false|301)#)\r\n','alpha',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(57,0,'alpha_form','default','body','div',2,'',0,34,'alpha','','\r\n','\r\n','',' <h3>Sign in using your Alpha Invitation Code</h3>\r\n          \r\n<form id=\"registerForm\" class=\"form-stacked\" name=\"alpha\" action=\"[root]/alpha_in\" method=\"post\">\r\n\r\n            \r\n            <fieldset>\r\n            <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"alpha_code\">Alpha Code</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required\" id=\"alpha_code\" name=\"alpha_code\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" value=\"(!(1)!)\"/>\r\n            </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n         <div class=\"clearfix\">\r\n            <label for=\"email\">Email Address</label>\r\n            <div class=\"input\">\r\n              <input class=\"xlarge required email\" id=\"email\" name=\"email\" size=\"30\" type=\"text\" />\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"actions\">    \r\n            <input type=\"submit\" class=\"btn primary\" value=\"Submit\">&nbsp;<button type=\"reset\" class=\"btn\">Reset</button>\r\n            </div>\r\n            \r\n            </fieldset>\r\n            </form>','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(58,0,'alpha_header','default','body','div',1,'page-header',0,31,'alpha|codes','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h1><a href=\"[root]\">Consent to Research</a> <small>Alpha Testing</small></h1>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(59,0,'alpha_help','default','body','div',0,'',0,35,'alpha','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h6>Help</h6>\r\n\r\n<p>If do not yet have an invitation but would like to join our alpha testing group, please sign up using the form at <a href=\"http://weconsent.us/alpha\">weconsent.us/alpha</a></p>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(60,0,'consent_form_1','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'','','\r\n','\r\n','','<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n <tbody><tr>\r\n  <td valign=\"top\" width=\"629\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span>Protocol Title:</span><b style=\"\"><span> Sage Bionetworks Common Genomics Research Database<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr style=\"\">\r\n  <td valign=\"top\" width=\"629\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">Principal Investigator: </span><b style=\"\">Stephen\r\n  Friend<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n <tr style=\"\">\r\n  <td valign=\"top\" width=\"629\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">Site-Responsible Investigator&#8217;s Institution:</span><b style=\"\"> Sage Bionetworks<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n     \r\n </tr>\r\n <tr style=\"\">\r\n  <td width=\"629\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">Description of Volunteer Population:</span><b style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"\">We are seeking a\r\n  diverse range of volunteers from a varied set of genetic, social and\r\n  environmental backgrounds to participate in common genomics research.\r\n  Volunteers must be willing to make their genetic and other health and human\r\n  trait information commonly available as part of this study. In order to\r\n  provide informed consent to participate, volunteers must be knowledgeable\r\n  about the science of genetics, the process of human subjects research and the\r\n  risks of participation in a common genomics research study of this nature.\r\n  Our goal is to create a database of common genomics information that can be\r\n  used for studies not yet imagined that connect genotypes to diseases, drug\r\n  response, and more.<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p> </o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"what_is_informed_consent\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"\">What is Informed\r\nConsent?<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; text-align: justify;\">Informed\r\nconsent means you understand the procedures, risks, possible benefits, and\r\nalternatives before you voluntarily agree to participate in a research\r\nstudy.<span style=\"\">  </span>Before you elect to participate,\r\nyou need to understand if or how this study may affect you and your\r\nfamily.<span style=\"\">  </span>This form, along with other\r\nstudy documents available on the study website <b style=\"\">[http://sagebase.org/commons]</b> (the &#8220;website&#8221;), is intended to help\r\nyou make an informed decision about your participation in this study.<span style=\"\">  </span>The website will be revised as needed, possibly\r\non a frequent basis, and participants and prospective participants should check\r\nthe website regularly to obtain the most current information about this study.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"why_have_you_been\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"\">Why have you been\r\nasked to participate in this research study</b><span class=\"MsoCommentReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><!--[if !supportAnnotations]--><span class=\"msocomanchor\"></span><span style=\"\"></span></span></span><b style=\"\">?<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; text-align: justify;\">You have\r\nbeen invited to participate because you meet the following minimum\r\nparticipation requirements for <b style=\"\">the Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project (CGRP)</b>:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 12pt 0.75in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">-<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">You understand\r\nthe concept of informed consent, the risks involved in common genomic research,\r\nand you wish to enroll in the CGRP. <o:p></o:p></i></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; text-align: justify;\">This <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject  </b>uses the <b style=\"\">Common Genomics Research\r\n(&#8220;CGR&#8221;) framework<span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></b></span><!--[endif]--></span></span></b>\r\nto identify potential participants for genomic research and biobanking projects\r\nwhich seek to broadly share participant data in order to benefit the common\r\ngood. Your completion of the CGR training modules, as well as your satisfaction\r\nof the minimum participant requirements listed above, mean that you are capable\r\nof providing informed consent to participate in <b style=\"\">the Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>. This\r\ndocument is intended to help you understand the benefits and risks of participating\r\nin CGR projects generally, and in <b style=\"\">the\r\nSage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> specifically.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"short_description\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"\">About the CGR Framework - Short Description</b><o:p></o:p></p><p>Traditionally, most scientific\r\nresearch has been a one-way process: individuals volunteer time and data in the\r\nname of improving our collective understanding. Small groups of researchers\r\nthen work to analyze that data and, hopefully, publish their findings in\r\nscientific literature. The aim of the Common Genomics Research framework is to\r\nallow participants, like you, to play a much more active role in the scientific\r\nresearch project. The CGR supports technical and legal tools that permit\r\nresearch participants to broadly share and distribute their data in the public\r\ndomain, fostering increased collaboration and creativity in the use of those\r\ndata. While the CGR believes that promoting public research is crucial to the rapid\r\nadvancement of scientific and medical knowledge, we also recognize that it\r\ncarries a unique set of risks and considerations for participants. This\r\ndocument is designed to help you understand those risks and to make an informed\r\nchoice about whether to participate in <b style=\"\">the\r\nSage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project.<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p id=\"long_description\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p><b style=\"\">About the CGR Framework - Long Description</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><i style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></i>This document lays out a process\r\nto create a framework for &#8220;Common Genomic Research&#8221; or CGR. This section of the\r\ndocument should help you to understand what we mean by each component of CGR: Common,\r\nGenomic, and Research, as well as some of the issues that surround CGR and the\r\nidea of informed consent. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>CGR is an idea that has come into\r\nexistence with the explosion of low-price, abundant gene sequencing &#8211; the\r\nconversion of the physical DNA in all of our cells into digital information\r\nrepresented as a series of letters (A, T, C, and G). Think of gene sequencing\r\nas the way we &#8220;read&#8221; our genomes into a format that allows computers to help us\r\nprocess, analyze, and understand how our DNA works.<span style=\"\">  </span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>When the first human genomes were\r\nsequenced, the cost per sequence was astronomical, more than $3,000,000,000\r\napiece. That cost has now dropped to under $1,000 and continues to drop, and is\r\nprojected to cost less than a new pair of designer athletic shoes by 2016. You\r\ncan get your entire genome sequenced for less than $5000 today, near the end of\r\n2011, a lossy full genome sequence (&#8220;exome&#8221;) for less than $1000, or a genetic\r\nvariation profile for less than $100. Tens of thousands of people have\r\npurchased their variation profiles, and the total number of full sequence\r\ngenomes is exploding.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>However, we have as yet not\r\nrealized the promises that were made in the race to sequence the genome. New\r\ndrug discovery is flat or even declining, and we seem to find new complexity\r\nwith each new tool that allows us to peer deeper into the physical operations\r\nof the human body. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>There is however one path forward\r\nthat holds tremendous promise, and does not require the invention of magical,\r\nrevolutionary technology: the assembly of a statistically powerful dataset of\r\ngenotypes connected to phenotypes &#8211; of the minute variations that make us\r\nindividual tied to the realities of our health, our lives, our bodies. If we\r\ncan assemble a large enough set of these genotype-phenotype combinations, it\r\nbecomes possible to use the same kinds of powerful statistical technologies\r\nthat power the Web to search for groups of genetic changes associated with a\r\nspecific disease, or with a group of people who take a cancer drug yet get no\r\nbenefit from it. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>All that stands between us and\r\nthis data set is our willpower. The technology exists to create the sequences\r\nand capture the phenotypes. The technology exists to store the data. The\r\ntechnology exists to find the correlations between genes and disease. And\r\nalthough our privacy laws make it complex to create a giant public data set out\r\nof these sequences and phenotypes, they do not make it impossible: they simply\r\nrequire that whoever&#8217;s genome is in that data makes the choice to do so with\r\nenough information to understand the choice: to provide informed consent.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>In general, people need to give\r\ninformed consent before they participate in the survey. In medical research,\r\nthe Nuremberg Code set a base international standard in 1947, and research\r\nproposals involving human subjects have developed since then. Most modern\r\nresearch is overseen by an ethics committee that also oversees the informed\r\nconsent process &#8211; and the Sage Common Genomics Research Project is no exception<span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span><!--[endif]--></span></span> as\r\nit is overseen by the Institutional Review Boards (IRB) for Sage Bionetworks.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"common_genomics_research\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Common Genomics Research</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>Here we unpack what we mean by Common\r\nGenomics Research by looking at each word in the phrase. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>By common, we mean that the data\r\nthat goes into the Sage Bionetworks database will be made available in an\r\n&#8220;open&#8221; manner &#8211; rather than trying to control who access the information, we&#8217;ll\r\ntry to increase the number of people who can see and use your data for\r\nresearch. This is the inverse of the old model, in which every study required\r\nits own informed consent process, and the data that emerged were private, not\r\nconnectable to data from other studies, and not available for studies that come\r\nafterwards. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>Common genomic research is not\r\nprecisely the same as &#8220;public genomic research&#8221; &#8211; a commons means that some\r\nrules do apply, that some rights are reserved, and there are some methods used\r\nto enforce those rules. Because common genomics comes with complications. Some\r\nusers might make a use of your data that you don&#8217;t like, or that can cause\r\nrisk. These risks are examined in detail in Article VI of this document. In\r\norder to mitigate those risks, we are taking a certain set of steps. First, we\r\nare going to require that anyone who accesses the data gives us their real\r\nnames. This allows us to associate user behavior with the real names of the\r\nuser, and creates a social incentive to behave. Second, we are going to require\r\nall users to sign a contract with us in which they agree to act in ways that\r\nare consistent with socially beneficial use of this data<span style=\"\">  </span>- to agree they will not try to reidentify\r\nyou, they will not harm you by raising your insurance rates, they will make\r\ntheir research results public, and they won&#8217;t transfer the data to anyone who\r\ndoesn&#8217;t play by the same rules. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>In fully public genomic research,\r\nthis set of rules is not applied, and data in public genomics are placed on the\r\nweb without any restrictions, identification of users, or other legal,\r\ntechnical, or normative conditions on use. The Personal Genome Project at\r\nHarvard Medical School is a good example of public genomic research.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>By genomic, we mean two kinds of\r\ndata. First, we mean your individual genomic data &#8211; both the sequences that we\r\nall share as humans, and the sequences that make us unique individuals. This is\r\n&#8220;static&#8221; genomic data in that it does not change after we are born, and usually\r\nwe only need to gather this once for any one person (although you may want to\r\nupgrade your genome data as newer, higher resolution machines to scan our\r\ngenomes become available, just as we upgrade our cameras as the number of\r\nmegapixels increases and allows us to take clearer pictures). Static genomic\r\ndata typically comes from sources such as cheek swabs, spit samples, and blood,\r\nand the samples are consumed as part of the sequencing process. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>But we also mean data about how\r\nyour genome reacts to certain situations, ranging from what you eat to how you\r\nrespond to a drug to how a disease is affecting you. This is &#8220;dynamic&#8221; genomic\r\ndata and it often comes from blood samples, tumor samples, and other tissue\r\nsamples, and it might be collected many times over the course of your life. The\r\nmachines that generate dynamic genomic data are rapidly evolving and\r\ndeveloping, and we will ask you to consent to a future-looking idea, that data\r\nwill be generated in the years to come using both machines we have today, like\r\ngene expression or methylation, but also by machines yet to be invented, and\r\nthat you may well provide samples over a multi-month or multi-year period as\r\nPGR becomes more and more powerful.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>For research, we allow many\r\ndifferent definitions. First, we mean traditional research in laboratories,\r\nwhich can happen in academic settings, corporate research laboratories, non\r\nprofit research foundations, and more. All of these kinds of research are\r\nallowed under the CGR framework. We do ask that publications emerging from CGR\r\nbased research are made available under &#8220;open access&#8221; terms, which means that\r\nall users of the Internet should have the right to read, download, and make\r\ncopies of the research that emerges from the information they upload. If a\r\nresearcher fails to comply we will not allow them to continue using the common\r\nresource. But we also mean a new form of research that is emerging from the\r\ninternet itself: the ability of small groups of patients and doctors to begin\r\nobserving themselves in small groups and making connections between their own\r\nhealth and their own genomes. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>We expect new forms of research\r\nto emerge rapidly, just as the second form has emerged unexpectedly in the past\r\nfew years. Thus, we have a very broad idea of research, one that can encompass\r\ninnovations in research methods as they develop. Primarily our goal is to\r\nensure that your data itself is not sold as a product, but that as many other\r\nuses as possible are enabled.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>To be clear, one of the goals of\r\nthe CGR is to <i style=\"\">facilitate the emergence of\r\n<b style=\"\"><u>products</u></b> that are built on\r\ncommon data</i>: new drugs, new diagnostics, software applications, hardware,\r\nand more. In consenting to CGR, you are consenting that your data may be used\r\nas a basis for the creation of these kinds of products. But your data itself\r\nwill be a common good, not a product.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>In order to create the commons we\r\ndescribe above, we must create a system that allows citizens to voluntarily\r\nenroll in common genomic research. Such a system is based on the idea of &#8220;informed\r\nconsent&#8221; &#8211; it&#8217;s a simple idea that says the group who is running a study should\r\ndisclose the risks of that study to the people that join the study, as well as\r\nthe risks that are important to an individual patient. Informed consent is\r\ndesigned to protect the people who enroll in studies from being harmed by\r\nunethical or poorly designed science. However, one of its unintended side\r\neffects is to make it hard to recombine data from studies with one another, and\r\nanother is to &#8220;lock up&#8221; the consent for a person inside a single study. So if\r\nyou enroll in five studies, you&#8217;ll consent five times, and no scientist can\r\ncome along later and put it all together in a way that is additive to learn\r\nmore about why your genome affects your health the way that it does.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><o:p></o:p>The consent process in the CGR\r\nuses a new approach, one we are calling Portable Legal Consent. Portable Legal\r\nConsent embeds the idea that we should disclose risks about research inside the\r\nidea that data should be something that can be remixed, to allow unexpected\r\ndiscoveries to emerge from the combination of earlier studies by later scientists.\r\nIf you complete the CGR process, you will have an informed consent that travels\r\nwith you from study to study, that travels with your data from study to study &#8211;\r\nthat is portable to you, and that is owned by you. Portable consent means that\r\nthe data you choose to upload into a CGR based system will be able to support a\r\nbroad range of genomic and health research without the unintended side effects\r\nof traditional consent.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"about_sage\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"\"></span><b style=\"\">About the Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 12pt; text-align: justify;\">Sage Bionetworks is conducting a study that\r\nwill harvest genomic, phenotypic, observational, and other forms of information\r\nabout individuals who have opted into a Common Genomic Research framework. The\r\nharvested data will be processed into a form that is machine-readable and can\r\nbe used to create connections between genetic variations and observable health\r\noutcomes from those variations, and in turn to facilitate the design of new\r\nstudies that test those connections to discover which are causing diseases, to\r\nfind new drugs, and advance our understanding and mapping of biology generally.\r\nThe harvested data will be available for redistribution and download to\r\nresearchers who have identified themselves to Sage Bionetworks by registering\r\nand signing the Terms of Use.<i style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></i></p>\r\n<p id=\"about_document\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"\">About this Informed Consent Document<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">This document is long, but we\r\nwant you to read through it so that you understand what it will mean for you to\r\nparticipate in the study.<span style=\"\">  </span>The table of\r\ncontents that follows is designed to help you more easily understand this consent\r\nform.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"\"><o:p> </o:p></b></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\">\r\n</span></b>\r\n','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(61,0,'consent_form_2','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'','','\r\n','\r\n','','\r\n<p id=\"article1\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE I.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">   \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">PURPOSE</span></span><span style=\"\"> of </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</span><br><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">\r\n<br>\r\n</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"text-transform: none; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none;\">Sage\r\nBionetworks is conducting a study that will harvest genomic, phenotypic,\r\nobservational, and other forms of information about individuals who have opted\r\ninto a Common Genomic Research framework. The harvested data will be processed\r\ninto a form that is machine-readable and can be used to create connections\r\nbetween genetic variations and observable health outcomes from those\r\nvariations, and in turn to facilitate the design of new studies that test those\r\nconnections to discover which are causing diseases, to find new drugs, and\r\nadvance our understanding and mapping of biology generally. The harvested data\r\nwill be available for redistribution and download to researchers who have\r\nidentified themselves to Sage Bionetworks by registering and signing the Terms\r\nof Use.</span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"article2\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE II.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">OVERVIEW</span></span></span><span style=\"\"> of </span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\"><i style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></i>Once you have completed the Portable Legal Consent\r\nprocess online, you will see a screen on your computer or other device (such as\r\na tablet) that allows you to begin uploading data. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">In the beginning, we will allow the upload of a small\r\nnumber of data types. If you have been genotyped (your genomic variation has\r\nbeen sequenced, or your full genome) then you will be able to upload the data\r\nfor harvesting into the Study. If you have a copy of your health record, such\r\nas those available under the US Government&#8217;s &#8220;Blue Button&#8221; format, you will be\r\nable to upload the data for harvesting into the Study. You will be able to take\r\na health survey, like those you take when you go to a new doctor for the first\r\ntime. You&#8217;ll also be able to upload other data about yourself that is just now\r\nemerging technically, ranging from day to day observations about things like\r\nyour weight to the data that your phone can capture that might be clinically\r\nimportant.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">It will always be your choice whether or not you want\r\nto upload any piece of data about yourself. Once you&#8217;ve uploaded data, it will\r\nbe integrated with data from other people who have gone through Portable\r\nConsent and uploaded their own data, and used to generate new insights about\r\nhealth and biology. You will be able to delete the copy that you uploaded at\r\nany time, but since Common Genomic Research is intended to create a network of\r\ndistributed and distributable data, we will probably not be able to retrieve\r\ncopies of your data that have already been distributed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article3\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nIII.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">    </span></span></span><span style=\"\">DURATION OF </span></span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">\r\nAND YOUR PARTICIPATION</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></span></p><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->This\r\nis an open-ended study that has no end date. We may choose to end the study at\r\nsome point, but currently plan to maintain the Sage Bionetworks Common Genomics\r\nProject as an ongoing common resource.</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><!--[endif]-->Your\r\nactive participation is up to you. Once you have gone through the Portable\r\nLegal Consent, you can upload data once and never return, or you can return\r\nagain and again to upload data as you get it, or to see what new kinds of data\r\nupload we have enabled since your last visit. It is completely your choice how\r\nlong you wish to be an active participant.</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"></span></span></span> The\r\nstudy will be hosted at Sage Bionetworks, which is itself hosted at the Fred\r\nHutchinson Cancer Clinic in Seattle, Washington, USA. Your participation will\r\nbe through the internet.</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"></span></span></span> The\r\nstudy is completely voluntary, at all points and in all ways.</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> There\r\nis no reimbursement of costs due to participation in the study.<o:p></o:p></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"></span> Part\r\nof the Portable Consent process creates a unique identifier for you that\r\ncreates the possibility for researchers to contact you without knowing who you\r\nare, so that you can choose to respond to requests to enroll in additional\r\nstudies, to learn about revisions or updates to this document, and so forth.\r\nThis choice will be voluntary and managed by the organization from which your\r\nPortable Consent was operated. The </span></span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </span>will make a public announcement at least once per year so that you might review and approve changes to this agreement.<span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"><br>  <br></span></span><o:p></o:p></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span id=\"article4\" style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nIV.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                     \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">Additional\r\nStudy PROCEDURES</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><i style=\"\">[reserved as necessary to\r\ndescribe additional steps to be taken by the participant prior to enrollment,\r\nduring participation, etc.]<o:p></o:p></i></span></p>\r\n<span style=\"\"></span><span style=\"\"></span>\r\n<p id=\"article5\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nV.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">Collection, publication and Return of data</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Collection of Baseline Data</u>. To enroll in this\r\nstudy you will be asked to provide the following baseline data (&#8220;Baseline\r\nData&#8221;): First Name, Last Name, Date of Birth, Email Address, Gender. This data\r\nwill be collected during the Portable Consent process and used to generate your\r\nunique ID and maintain a record of whether or not you wish to be recontacted.\r\nOnly your unique ID, birth year, and gender will be harvested for\r\nredistribution. These fields will be free-entry except for Date of Birth and\r\nGender.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Collection of Molecular Data</u>. This project will\r\nnot generate molecular data directly, but will instead collect data that you\r\nhave generated yourself either through Direct to Consumer services or via\r\ninteractions with other health care or research projects. Molecular data\r\nincludes, but is not limited to, your &#8220;static&#8221; genome data, your &#8220;dynamic&#8221;\r\ngenome data, and other measurements that can emerge from your body.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(a)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Static genome data.</u> This is the gene sequence\r\nthat is carried in all of your cells. We call it &#8220;static&#8221; genome data because\r\nit does not change over time &#8211; your gene sequence is unique to you. Static\r\ngenome data can also include multiple sequences from the same person &#8211; for\r\nexample, a cancer patient might have a skin genome sequence, a blood genome,\r\nand a tumor genome sequence. Examples of static genome data include, but are\r\nnot limited to, genotypes (partial sequences of your genome, such as those\r\nprovided by 23andme), exome sequences, and full genomes. We say that it\r\nincludes, but is not limited to, these types because the machinery to examine\r\nour genomes is improving at incredible speed, and we want to make sure that\r\nthis agreement does not have to be revised every time an innovative advance is\r\nmade in the field.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(b)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Dynamic genome data</u>. This is data about how your\r\ngenome reacts to the environment you live in: to diet, to medicines, to\r\ndisease, to exercise, and more. The genes in your genome turn on and off in\r\nresponse to these kinds of external stimuli, and being able to measure which\r\ngenes are turned on or off in a given situation is essential to understanding\r\nwhy and how the genome affects day to day health. Examples of dynamic genome\r\ndata include, but are not limited to, gene expression, RNA expression,\r\nmethylation, and more. We say that it includes, but is not limited to, these types\r\nbecause the machinery to examine our genomes is improving at incredible speed,\r\nand we want to make sure that this agreement does not have to be revised every\r\ntime an innovative advance is made in the field. It is unlikely, though not\r\nimpossible, that most patients will have this kind of data about themselves.\r\nBut, it is very likely that if patients submit biological samples, that this\r\nkind of data is being generated &#8211; and that patients will have the right through\r\nother mechanisms to a copy of the data about themselves and then upload into a\r\nCGR framework or authorize a researcher to upload it on his or her behalf.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(c)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Other measurements</u>. There is an explosion in our\r\ncapacity to gather data about the body, not just our genomes. We can now make\r\nan enormous set of measurements from a tiny drop of blood or urine, for example\r\n&#8211; to determine blood sugar levels, test cholesterol, look for allergies, and\r\nmore. Doctors and clinical researchers often use this data in diagnosing\r\npatients and prescribing treatment regimes, so it&#8217;s vital that you be able to\r\nupload this kind of data once you have access to your health records. This is\r\ndata that researchers can combine with static and dynamic genomic data to turn\r\ninto &#8220;models&#8221; of activity, so that we can start to tie the activities of\r\ndoctors back to our genomes. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.3<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Collection of Other data.</u> So far we have focused\r\non data that is deeply tied to your body: your genome, its activity, and your\r\ntissues. But there is an enormous amount of data about your lifestyle that is\r\nnot covered: how often you exercise, what you eat, how you live. This is data\r\nthat can be gathered in any number of ways: via surveys, games, applications on\r\nphones, direct interactions with doctors, direct interactions with other\r\npatients, and more. This is data that has enormous potential value, and it is\r\ndata that is increasingly under your control. We leave this definition\r\nintentionally vague, because it will be your choice what kinds of data about\r\nyour lifestyle you would like to upload &#8211; but if you choose to upload it, that\r\ndata will become part of the CGR framework. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.4<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Publication of Your Data</u>. \r\n    <p>The Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project utilizes the CGR framework, which means that it has committed to publishing the data it collects and generates in the most widely accessible and publicly useful format possible. As part of your participation in this project, the personal data described above will be distributed via a database protected by password and available only to researchers who have registered and signed a contract agreeing to the user requirements of the CGR by Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project and included as part of the CGR common database. A discussion of the risks associated with publishing the data gathered by Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project in the PGR public database may be found in Article VI.</p>\r\n    <u>No Obligation</u>. As a participant you are under no\r\nobligation to provide any data or information.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>However, you may not be able to participate in other aspects of <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b>, until you supply the data or information described above or\r\notherwise requested.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.6<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Guarantees</u>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>Due to factors ranging from funding uncertainty to technological\r\nchallenges, the <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b> cannot make any guarantees about the accuracy,\r\ncompleteness or process time of any analysis, research or interpretation\r\ndescribed in this section.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">5.7<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Limited Ability to Withdraw</u>. Due to the nature of\r\nthe PGR framework, your ability to fully withdraw from <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> once some or all\r\nof the data described above has been published may be limited, as described in <b style=\"\">Article II.</b><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article6\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nVI.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                     \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">RISKS AND\r\nDISCOMFORTS</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">The CGR framework is designed to facilitate the\r\ndevelopment of a new form of public scientific research where participants play\r\na more active role in the management of their research experience and data, and\r\nto encourage the wide dissemination and active discussion of research data and\r\nresults.<span style=\"\">  </span>Because this endeavor is\r\nrelatively new, and because scientific research inherently breaks new\r\ntechnological and cultural ground, it is impossible to accurately predict all\r\nof the possible risks and discomforts that you might experience as a result of\r\nyour participation in this study.<span style=\"\">  </span>In\r\nthis section you will read about the risks that we have identified as\r\npotentially relevant to your participation in research projects adopting the CGR\r\nframework, like <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">You are strongly encouraged to think carefully about\r\nthese risks, as well as any other risks or discomforts that you anticipate\r\nmight arise as a result of your own unique circumstances.<span style=\"\">  </span>These might include your own health or\r\nmedical conditions, your family and personal relationships or any other factor\r\nthat is specific to you.<span style=\"\">  </span>In addition to\r\nunderstanding the risks outlined in this <b style=\"\">Article\r\n</b><!--[if supportFields]><b style=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-spacerun:yes\'> </span>REF _Ref286989844 w h t * MERGEFORMAT <span\r\nstyle=\'mso-element:field-separator\'></span></b><![endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"AR-SA\">&#8206;</span><b style=\"\">VI<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:data>08D0C9EA79F9BACE118C8200AA004BA90B02000000080000000E0000005F005200650066003200380036003900380039003800340034000000</w:data>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></b><!--[if supportFields]><b style=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:\r\nnormal\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></b><![endif]-->, you should\r\nfeel confident that you have sufficient knowledge (via the educational and\r\ntesting materials available on the CGR and <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</span>\r\nwebsites or through other sources) of genetics, human subjects research and the\r\nbenefits and risks of participation in this study to make an informed decision\r\nabout whether participation is right for you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">You are <b style=\"\">strongly\r\nencouraged<span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></b></span></span></span></b>\r\nto discuss this study and its potential risks with your immediate family\r\nmembers as well as with your doctor and/or other qualified health care\r\nproviders.<span style=\"\">  </span>You are also encouraged to discuss\r\nwith the Principal Investigator directly any additional concerns that you may\r\nhave regarding the risks to you of participating in this study.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\">Finally, because the science in this area is evolving,\r\nand data will be collected on an ongoing basis by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>, the risks\r\ninvolved due to your participation in this study, as well as the likelihood and\r\nseverity of such risks, will change over time.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>You will not be asked to review and re-sign this consent form every time\r\nnew information related to the risk of participation becomes available.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, the CGR and <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> will try to\r\nupdate this consent form and the study website as frequently as possible to\r\nreflect the latest information about the risks of participation.<span style=\"\">  </span>Participants and prospective participants are\r\nstrongly encouraged to check the website regularly and to update their contact\r\ninformation with both the CGR and <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> in order to obtain the most\r\ncurrent information regarding the risks and discomforts of participation.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiCont1\"><b style=\"\">Please remember\r\nthat you are free not to participate if you have not already enrolled, and to\r\nwithdraw at any time if you have already enrolled in the study.<o:p></o:p></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">6.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Risks Associated with the Publication of Your Data</u>.</span><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span><!--[endif]--></span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(a)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks\r\nCommon Genomic Research Project </b>will require users to register, provide\r\nusernames and contact information, and sign a contract imposing certain\r\nbehaviors on them that are part of the Commons. Users of the data will have to\r\nagree not to attempt to re-identify you, not to &#8220;harm&#8221; you (a general category\r\nmeaning that you will not be discriminated against as a result of what is in\r\nyour genome, described below), and to publish the results of their research in\r\na way that allows you to read the research papers free of charge. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nHowever, this is a lightweight system of protection. It is possible that data\r\ncan be accidentally disclosed, or maliciously extracted and republished without\r\nthese protections. <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks\r\nCommon Genomic Research Project </b>will evict users who behave this way but\r\ncannot guarantee that your data will never become truly public. Thus, we\r\nbelieve it is ethically vital that you understand and consent to the risks\r\nassociated with public disclosure of your data, even though your data is moving\r\ninto the commons instead.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(b)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Risks Associated\r\nwith Public Disclosure</i>.<span style=\"\">  </span>The risks of\r\npublic disclosure of your genetic and trait data, including your DNA sequence\r\ndata, or other information you provide, could affect the employment, insurance\r\nand financial well-being or social interactions of you and your immediate\r\nfamily.<span style=\"\">  </span>The following is a\r\nnon-comprehensive list of hypothetical scenarios that could pose risks for you\r\nand/or your family:<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(i)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->The public disclosure of your genetic and trait data\r\ncould cause you to learn &#8211; either directly, from a family member or from\r\nanother individual &#8211; certain unexpected genealogical features about you and/or\r\nyour family.<span style=\"\">  </span>This could include\r\ninferences or allegations that your relationships with family members or other\r\nindividuals, or your ancestral or cultural origins, are different than you had\r\npreviously believed.<span style=\"\">  </span>In particular, this\r\ncould include inferences of non-paternity, as well as inferences or allegations\r\nof paternity made by individuals you did not previously know or suspect were\r\nrelated to you.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(ii)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Anyone with sufficient knowledge and resources could\r\ntake your DNA sequence data and/or posted trait information and use that data,\r\nwith or without changes, to :<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL6\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(A)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->accurately or inaccurately reveal to you or a member of\r\nyour family the possibility of a disease or other trait or propensity for a\r\ndisease or other trait;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL6\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(B)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->claim statistical evidence, including with respect to\r\nyour genetic predisposition to certain diseases or other traits, that could\r\naffect the ability of you and/or your family to obtain or maintain employment,\r\ninsurance or financial services;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL6\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(C)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->claim relatedness to criminals or other notorious\r\nfigures or groups on the part of you and/or your family;<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL6\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(D)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->correctly or incorrectly associate you and/or your\r\nrelatives with ongoing or unsolved criminal investigations on the basis of your\r\npublicly available genetic data; or<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL6\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(E)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->make synthetic DNA and plant it at a crime scene, or\r\notherwise use it to falsely identify or implicate you and/or your family.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(iii)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Whether or not it is lawful to do so, you could be\r\nsubject to actual or attempted employment, insurance, financial, or other forms\r\nof discrimination or negative treatment due to the public disclosure of your\r\ngenetic and trait information by the <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> or by a third party.<span style=\"\">  </span>Although the United States has a law that\r\nbars certain forms of genetic discrimination (the Genetic Information\r\nNondiscrimination Act, also known as GINA), this law does not apply to the use\r\nof genetic information in all circumstances and, even where it does apply, it\r\ndoes not guarantee that your genetic information will not be used against you\r\nin a way that you feel is discriminatory or otherwise harmful to you and/or\r\nyour family.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(iv)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->If you have previously made available or intend to make\r\navailable genetic or other medical or trait information in a confidential\r\nsetting, for example in another research study, the data that you provide to <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> may be used, on its own or in combination with your previously\r\nshared data, to identify you as a participant in otherwise private and/or\r\nconfidential research.<span style=\"\">  </span>This means that\r\nany data or other information you may have shared pursuant to a promise of\r\nconfidentiality or privacy may become public despite your intent that they be\r\nkept private and confidential.<span style=\"\">  </span>This\r\ncould result in certain adverse effects for you, including ones not considered\r\nor anticipated by this consent form.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(v)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Data that you provide (such as trait data or DNA sequence or other genetic data) may be used to identify you,\r\nresulting in contact from the press and other members of the public motivated\r\nby positive or negative feelings about the study.<span style=\"\">  </span>This could mean a significant loss of privacy\r\nand personal time.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(vi)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Your publicly available DNA sequence data, trait data\r\nand other information will include certain information that applies to your\r\nfamily members.<span style=\"\">  </span>Some people may draw\r\nconclusions from your publicly available information, including speculating\r\nabout what such information might reveal about you and your family\r\nmembers.<span style=\"\">  </span>As a result, <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> cannot predict all of the risks, or the severity of the risks, that\r\nthe public availability of this information may pose to you and your\r\nrelatives.<span style=\"\">  </span>You are strongly encouraged\r\nto discuss this study and its potential risks, including the fact that not all\r\nof the risks are known, with your immediate family members.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(c)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Possibility of\r\nUnintended Public Disclosure</i>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you\r\nenroll in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>, it is possible that data not intended to be\r\npublished <b style=\"\">(e.g., your name, date of\r\nbirth, or contact information)</b><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></b></span><!--[endif]--></span></b></span></span><span style=\"\"> will be publicly disclosed due to unintended\r\ndata breaches, including hacking or other activities outside of the procedures\r\nauthorized by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Should\r\nthis occur you would be subject to the various risks and discomforts described\r\nin this section and throughout this consent form, and possibly to other risks\r\nas well, even though you did not intend for such data to be published.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(d)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Reproduction or\r\nModification of your Data</i>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you\r\nchoose to make your DNA sequence data and other information available, it will\r\nbe published by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project </b>through the CGR common database and/or in other\r\nsimilar formats, and will be available<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> </span><b style=\"\">with\r\nthe restrictions described in 6.1 (a)</b><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></b></span><!--[endif]--></span></b></span></span><span style=\"\"> to third parties.<span style=\"\">  </span>As a result, neither you nor the <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> will be able to control or restrict the access, use, reproduction,\r\nmodification or analysis of your data and other public information<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> beyond those conditions in 6.1 (a)</span>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Your data and other public information may be\r\nmade public in other forms in addition to its inclusion in the CGR common\r\ndatabase.<span style=\"\">  </span>It may also be altered, without\r\nyour knowledge or your consent, in a way that might be inaccurate and or\r\nupsetting to you.<span style=\"\">  </span>For example, a third\r\nparty could access your publicly available sequence data or other information,\r\nchange it and republish it to suggest that you had a propensity for a disease\r\nor other detrimental trait.<span style=\"\">  </span>Additional\r\nadverse effects are also possible.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(e)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Data Not to be\r\nUsed for Medical Care</i>.<span style=\"\">  </span>The data you\r\nupload to <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>, including research data, specimen analysis data\r\n(including your DNA sequence data) or any other reports, interpretations or\r\nfindings generated or provided to you by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>, are not an appropriate\r\nsubstitute for professional medical or clinical advice, diagnosis or treatment,\r\nand may not be used by you for any medical or clinical purpose unless first\r\nconfirmed by a licensed healthcare professional.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(i)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Medical doctors do not routinely screen DNA sequence\r\ndata for genetic variations comprehensively.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>Gene-specific sequencing is routinely performed but usually in the\r\ncontext of a positive personal or family medical history consistent with\r\ncurrently known genetic disorders.<span style=\"\">  </span>As such,\r\nthe clinical importance of this data is not known with any certainty at this\r\ntime for any population-based, genomic study like <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>The validity of many genetic associations,\r\nwhen screened for in the general population, remains uncertain.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(ii)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Regardless of any specific interpretations or findings\r\nmade available to you by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>, you are likely to be\r\nsubjected to additional interpretations &#8211; both accurate and inaccurate &#8211; of\r\nyour public data by people outside of the study.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(f)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Risks Due to\r\nPursuing Health or Medical Care</i>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>Your specimen analysis data (including your DNA sequence data) and\r\ninterpretations or findings about your data may contain potentially alarming\r\ninformation, such as potentially harmful genetic variants.<span style=\"\">  </span>This may cause you to experience anxiety or\r\nstress.<span style=\"\">  </span>As a result, you may want to\r\nseek health or medical care or counseling to verify the accuracy of such\r\ninterpretations, whether provided by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>or by other sources.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you choose to pursue health or medical\r\ncare or counseling, you could be exposed to additional risks and/or\r\ndiscomforts, several of which are identified below.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(g)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">You are Responsible\r\nFor Your Own Health or Medical Care</i>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>Neither <b style=\"\">the CGR entity<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"> operating an instance of the consent framework </span></b><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><b style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></b></span></span></b></span></span><span style=\"\">or <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> will (i)\r\nprovide you with, (ii) arrange for, (iii) pay for, reimburse you for or otherwise subsidize\r\nor (iv) provide you, your doctor or any other health\r\ncare provider or insurer with any recommendations, advice or other guidance\r\nwith respect to, any of your health or medical care, including any current or\r\nfollow-up medical or clinical advice, counseling, diagnosis, treatment,\r\npreventative action or other related course of action of any kind.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(i)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> is a research study and is not\r\nresponsible for any part of your health or medical care, including, accurately\r\npredicting disease or disease risk, informing you of genetic variations or\r\nproviding you with accurate and valid DNA sequence data or interpretations of\r\nyour DNA sequence data.<span style=\"\">  </span>No health or\r\nmedical care of any kind will be made available by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> and, as\r\ndescribed above, no special arrangements, for compensation or otherwise, will\r\nbe made by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b> should you require or choose to pursue any health\r\nor medical care as a result of your participation in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(ii)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->You should talk to your doctor or other qualified\r\nhealth care provider if you have questions about any of your genetic or trait\r\ninformation, including your specimen analysis data (including DNA sequence\r\ndata) or any other interpretations or findings based on your data, whether or\r\nnot provided by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>You\r\nshould not ignore professional medical advice from your doctor or any other\r\nqualified health care provider about any of your genetic or trait data or other\r\ninformation provided or analyzed by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>You should not interpret any analysis,\r\ninterpretation or finding provided by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> as recommending or\r\ndiscouraging any specific treatment plan, product, or course of action with\r\nrespect to your health or medical care.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(iii)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->If after talking with your doctor or other qualified\r\nhealth care provider, you decide that any change in your health or medical care\r\nis necessary or advisable as a result of any information or interpretation you\r\nhave received due to your participation in <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</span>,\r\nyou will be solely responsible for all resulting payments and costs associated\r\nwith such health or medical care.<span style=\"\">  </span>You\r\nwill also be solely responsible for consulting with your doctor, your health\r\ncare provider and your health care insurance provider, if any, to determine\r\nwhether any such costs would be covered or reimbursed.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(iv)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">            \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Any health or medical care that you may determine is necessary,\r\nafter consultation with your doctor or other qualified health care provider and\r\nwhether as a result of your participation in this study or otherwise, may be\r\ninvasive and have its own associated risks and expenses.<span style=\"\">  </span>Serious risks, including death, may be\r\ninvolved in any such health or medical care.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>You should carefully consider these risks, as well as whether you have\r\nthe financial and other resources necessary to pursue such health or medical\r\ncare.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL5\" style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(v)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->If your doctor or other qualified health care provider\r\nis directly or indirectly involved with <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>, as either a researcher or a\r\nparticipant, any health or medical care that you receive from such health care\r\nprovider, including medical advice or clinical management, represents health or\r\nmedical care provided by that provider pursuant to your existing doctor-patient\r\nrelationship, and is not health or medical care provided by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b>.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; page-break-after: avoid;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">6.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Physical Risks and Discomforts</u>.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(a)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">              \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->There is no physical participation required for this study. If you are physically injured as a result or your\r\nparticipation in this study, please seek medical care immediately and contact\r\nthe Principal Investigator.<span style=\"\">  </span><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> will not provide any health or medical care to participants.<o:p></o:p></p>','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(62,0,'consent_form_3','default','body','div',0,'',0,0,'','','\r\n','\r\n','','<p id=\"article7\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nVII.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                  \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">BENEFITS</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">7.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Benefits to You</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>You are not likely to benefit in any way as a\r\nresult of your participation in the <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">7.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Data return.</u> If you enroll in a study that takes\r\na biosample from you, and that study uses the CGR framework, either through\r\nthis Consent Agreement or through another one that is deemed interoperable by\r\nthe Consent to Research project, then you will be entitled to a copy of the raw\r\nmolecular data that is generated from your biosample. You will not be entitled\r\nto processed, interpreted, or other versions of the data, and the caveats about\r\nmedical care laid out in Article VI apply to this data as well. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article8\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nVIII.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">INTELLECTUAL\r\nPROPERTY</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">8.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Promoting Open Access</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>One of the primary goals of the CGR framework\r\nis to develop public datasets supplied by willing research participants to aid\r\nin the development of analytical tools and interfaces for scientists, doctors,\r\nand individuals around the world.<span style=\"\">  </span>In\r\norder to accomplish this, the PGR endeavors to develop licenses, data\r\nstructures and other tools to maximize the ability of the study to share its\r\ndata in the broadest possible fashion, and <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> has adopted these principles.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">8.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Ownership of Your Information and Data</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Neither <b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b> nor <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b> will attempt to assert ownership of any\r\ninformation or data that you provide</span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\">[10]</span></span><!--[endif]--></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">\r\ndirectly to </span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\"> </b>as part of\r\nyour participation in the study.</span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\">[11]</span></span><!--[endif]--></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">  </span>However, by participating in the study you\r\ngrant to <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project </b>and </span></span><span style=\"\"> <b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> a nonexclusive, worldwide, royalty free, perpetual, irrevocable\r\nlicense to use such information and data without restriction including, without\r\nlimitation, the right to sublicense, copy, distribute, transmit, publicly\r\ndisplay and perform, publish, reproduce, edit, translate, reformat and create\r\nderivative works.<span style=\"\">  </span>This grant of rights\r\nis subject only to your ability to withdraw from the study, as described in <b style=\"\">Article </b></span></span><!--[if supportFields]><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Ref286989884\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc289807706\'></span></span><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Ref286989884\'><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc289807706\'><b style=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-spacerun:yes\'> </span>REF _Ref286989896 \\w \\h \\t \\* MERGEFORMAT <span\r\nstyle=\'mso-element:field-separator\'></span></b></span></span><![endif]--><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\" lang=\"AR-SA\">&#8206;</span><b style=\"\">X<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:data>08D0C9EA79F9BACE118C8200AA004BA90B02000000080000000E0000005F005200650066003200380036003900380039003800390036000000</w:data>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></b></span></span><!--[if supportFields]><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Ref286989884\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc289807706\'></span></span><span\r\nstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span><![endif]--><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> of this consent form.</span></span>\r\nWhat this means is that users will be able to remix, build upon, and under\r\ncertain conditions, make copies of the data you upload, without complex\r\nownership conditions other than those in the user Terms of Use.<i style=\"\"> </i><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">8.3<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Ownership of your Information and Data</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Any information, data, analyses or other\r\nmaterials created or prepared by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> from such tissue samples or\r\nspecimens, including, without limitation, your DNA sequence data, cell lines\r\nand the results of any research or analysis performed by or in collaboration\r\nwith <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic\r\nResearch Project</b>, are the property of and owned by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> and not by\r\nyou.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, consistent with the goals\r\nof the CGR framework, <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks\r\nCommon Genomic Research Project</b> and this consent form, <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> will attempt to make this information, data or materials,\r\nincluding your DNA sequence data, cell lines and other related analyses and\r\nmaterials, freely available to you and/or to the public as described in this\r\nconsent form.<span style=\"\">  </span>Ultimately, however, it\r\nwill be <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic\r\nResearch Project</b>&#8217;s decision &#8211; consistent with the requirements imposed by </span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\">, this consent form, <b style=\"\">[sponsoring institution]</b> and applicable\r\nlaw &#8211; when and whether to make available such information, data and\r\nmaterials.<span style=\"\">  </span><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> is unable to\r\nguarantee if, when or in what form you will receive access to any information,\r\ndata or materials as part of your participation in this study.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">8.4<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Licensing for Profit</u></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><u><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></u></span><!--[endif]--></span></u></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">.<span style=\"\">  </span>Other than for purposes of recovering its\r\ncosts, <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic\r\nResearch Project</b> will not license or otherwise make available your data\r\nand personal information to any person, institution, company or other third\r\nparty for the financial gain or commercial profit of <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Any information or data included in the CGR\r\npublic database will be made available under a <b style=\"\">CC0 license </b>and will not be licensed for commercial profit by </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, information that you provide will be\r\nmade available to third parties for research, patient care, commercial or other\r\npurposes, and these third parties may commercially profit from the data or\r\nother information that you contribute to <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>and the CGR common database.</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">8.5<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Compensation</u></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><u><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></u></span></span></u></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">.<span style=\"\">  </span>You will not be compensated for your\r\nparticipation in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks\r\nCommon Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>The results of studies using materials provided by you may have\r\ncommercial potential.<span style=\"\">  </span>Neither you nor\r\nyour heirs will receive financial or any other benefits from any discoveries,\r\nwhether or not of a commercial nature, made using the information and/or\r\nspecimens that you provide.</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article9\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nIX.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                     \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">CONFIDENTIALITY</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">9.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Limited Confidentiality After Publication</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you are enrolled in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> and choose to\r\npublish any of your data</span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span><!--[endif]--></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> through\r\nthe CGR common database, those data will be kept or made available by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> or by </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> in a limited\r\nconfidential fashion.<span style=\"\">  </span><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject </b>and </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\"></b> will\r\nrequire any collaborators or other individuals accessing your information to maintain\r\nsuch information in a de-identified\r\nfashion.<span style=\"\">  </span>Unless you withdraw from the\r\nstudy before your data are distributed, your genetic and trait data will be\r\nmade available via a commonly accessible database with user controls and terms\r\nof use that protect confidentiality, but cannot guarantee complete\r\nconfidentiality.</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">9.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Association of Your Name With Your Data</u>.</span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span>Neither <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>nor </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\"> </b>will intentionally associate your name with your\r\ngenomic or trait data or other information that is published to the PGR public\r\ndatabase or otherwise intentionally identify you as a participant in <span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b></span> without your prior consent.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, as described above, because of the\r\nidentifiable nature of the information you provide to <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>, as well as the nature\r\nof the data and analyses generated by </span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">\r\n</b>and the common nature of the CGR database, it is possible that one or more\r\nthird parties may identify you as a participant in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>This may result in the association of your\r\npublished data and other information with your name or other information that\r\nyou have not provided to <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> and may not have wished to be\r\npublicly disclosed.</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">9.3<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Direct Disclosure to Your Health Care Provider</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Your genetic and trait data will not be sent\r\nto your health care provider directly by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> and will not become part of\r\nyour medical record due to any direct activities of <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, because this information will be commonly\r\navailable, and may be identified as yours, it could become part of your medical\r\nrecord or be shared with your doctor or other health care provider or your\r\nhealth care insurance provider, or provided to others due to the activities of\r\none or more third parties.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<span style=\"\"></span>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">9.4<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">             \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Publication of Results</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>The results of <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> may be published\r\nin a medical book, journal, website or webpage, or used for teaching\r\npurposes.<span style=\"\">  </span>Identifying information that\r\nis associated with your data and/or the results of this study (such as your\r\nphotograph, DNA sequence data, and medical or trait information, as well as\r\nyour name if that has become associated with your study data by a third party\r\nduring the course of your participation in <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>), may be used in such\r\npublications or teaching materials.<span style=\"\">  </span><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b> will not notify you prior to such uses.<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article10\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nX.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\"> </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">REFUSAL OR WITHDRAWAL OF PARTICIPATION</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">10.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Voluntary Participation</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Participation in this study is\r\nvoluntary.<span style=\"\">  </span>You do not have to\r\nparticipate in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>You may\r\nwithdraw your participation (including your data, subject to the limitations\r\nbelow) from this study at any time.<span style=\"\">  </span>You\r\nwill never have to provide a reason for your withdrawal.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">10.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Limitations on Withdrawal</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>You are free to decide at any time that you\r\nno longer want your data or other information to be used as part of this\r\nstudy.<span style=\"\">  </span>However, it may not be possible\r\nto prevent the future use of your data or other information in certain\r\ncircumstances:</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL4\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">(a)<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">               \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><i style=\"\">Deletion of Trait\r\nand Sequence Data</i>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you choose to\r\nwithdraw from the study and request that your genetic and trait data to be\r\nremoved, you will send your unique Sage Bionetworks Common Identifier to the project and within <span style=\"\">6</span><span style=\"\"> months <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> will delete all DNA sequence\r\nand trait data about you held by <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>and will notify </span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework </b></span><span style=\"\">of your withdrawal from <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b>.<span style=\"\">  </span>Both </span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"> and <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>will take reasonable steps to\r\nensure that the data provided by you or generated by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>will not be\r\nincluded in future updates to the CGR public database.</span><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>However, once any data or information about you is posted to the CGR\r\npublic database, other organizations and individuals may acquire copies of\r\nit.<span style=\"\">  </span>There will be no way to ensure that\r\nthey will delete their copies of your data or information, or for <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject </b>or </span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"> to even\r\nknow what copies of your data or information may exist.<span style=\"\">  </span>Both <b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project </b>and </span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"> will encourage researchers and other users to use the\r\nmost current version of the CGR public database, but your data may be combined\r\nby <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic\r\nResearch Project</b> and/or its collaborators or other third parties in ways\r\nthat will make it impossible to delete them from such datasets.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">10.3<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Removal from the Study</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span><b style=\"\">Sage\r\nBionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> may decide to end your\r\nparticipation in this study at any time.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>If <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common\r\nGenomic Research Project</b> terminates your participation it may provide you\r\nwith an explanation.<span style=\"\">  </span>If your participation\r\nin <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic\r\nResearch Project </b>is terminated, you may ask that <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b> destroy or\r\ndelete any of your data in accordance with the provisions set forth above.<span style=\"\">  </span>If neither you nor your Designated Proxy</span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportFootnotes]--><span class=\"MsoFootnoteReference\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\"></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\">\r\nrequest that your data be destroyed or deleted upon the conclusion of your\r\nparticipation in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks\r\nCommon Genomic Research Project</b>, your data may be maintained by <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject </b>consistent with this consent form and included indefinitely in the\r\nPGR public database.</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">10.4<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Maintenance of Certain Information</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you decide to withdraw, or if </span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b></span><span style=\"\"> ends your participation, </span><span style=\"\"><span style=\"\"> </span></span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">the CGR\r\nentity who runs an instance of the Consent framework</b></span><span style=\"\"> may continue to keep certain limited information about you following the conclusion\r\nof your participation in </span><span style=\"\"><b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research\r\nProject</b></span><span style=\"\">,\r\nincluding your name, date of first participation, date of enrollment, date of\r\ntermination or withdrawal and reason for termination or withdrawal.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article11\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nXI.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                     \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">ALTERNATIVES</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">11.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Alternative</u>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>The alternative is not to participate in <b style=\"\">Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</b>.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">11.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>No Effect</u>.<span style=\"\"> \r\n</span>If you choose not to participate, your medical treatment by your doctor\r\nor other health care providers will not be affected.</span><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p id=\"article12\" class=\"RBHTraditiL1\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"\">ARTICLE\r\nXII.<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">                  \r\n</span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"\">RESEARCH-RELATED\r\nCONTACT INFORMATION:</span></span><span style=\"\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">12.1<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Principal Investigator</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If\r\nyou have any questions or concerns about\r\nthe study, or if you suffer a research related injury, you may contact\r\nthe\r\nPrincipal Investigator: Stephen Friend, at Sage Bionetworks. The\r\naddress is 1100 Fairview Ave. N, Mailstop M1-C108, Seattle WA USA\r\n98109. Telephone +1 (206) 667-2062. </span></p><p class=\"RBHTraditiL3\" style=\"margin-left: 0in;\"><span style=\"\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"\">12.2<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">         \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><u>Additional Contact Information</u>.<span style=\"\">  </span>If you wish to discuss your rights as a\r\nparticipant in a research study, or if you feel under any pressure to enroll in\r\nthis study you may contact: [<i style=\"\">IRB / OHRP\r\ncontact information</i>]</span><b style=\"\"><u> <o:p></o:p></u></b></p>','\r\n','',0,0,'','',0,'\r\n','',0,0,0,'',1,2,'w'),(63,0,'agreement_help','default','body','div',0,'',0,35,'consent/agreement','','\r\n','\r\n','','<h6>Table of Contents</h6>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#what_is_informed_consent\">What is Informed Consent?</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#why_have_you_been\">Why have you been asked to participate in this research study?</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#short_description\">Short Description of the CGR Framework</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#long_description\">Long Description of the CGR Framework</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#common_genomics_research\">Common Genomics Research</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#about_sage\">About the Sage Bionetworks Common Genomic Research Project</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"#about_document\">About this Informed Consent Document</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE I. <a href=\"#article1\">PURPOSE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE II. <a href=\"#article2\">OVERVIEW</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE III. <a href=\"#article3\">DURATION of Study</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE IV. <a href=\"#article4\">Additional Study PROCEDURES</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE V. <a href=\"#article5\">Collection, publication and Return of data</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE VI. <a href=\"#article6\">RISKS AND DISCOMFORTS</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE VII. <a href=\"#article7\">BENEFITS</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE VIII. <a href=\"#article8\">INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE IX. <a href=\"#article9\">CONFIDENTIALITY</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE X. <a href=\"#article10\">REFUSAL OR WITHDRAWAL OF PARTICIPATION</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ARTICLE XI. <a href=\"#artic